          "date": "2013-10-10 18:57:38.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-2528 misc: quiet warning for 2.1/2.5 connections",
        "message": "LU-2528 misc: quiet warning for 2.1/2.5 connections\n\nThe Lustre 2.1 client prints a warning about connections with servers\nnewer than Lustre 2.3, yet they are still interoperable.  Increase\nthe window of warning to be up to Lustre 2.5.50, since we do not\nplan to allow interoperability between 2.1 and 2.6 systems.  This\nwas from the time when major releases like Lustre 1.4 and 1.8 would\nwere years apart and had no chance for interoperation.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I451d3f559d78a93361255061c93d36e27b3ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
